-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Augusta Resource, Canadian Pacific Railway
-- 
-- Thu Jun 26, 2014 04:24AM EDT
-- None



June 26 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Augusta Resource and Canadian Pacific Railway, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Augusta Resource <AZC.TO>: CIBC cuts to sector performer from sector outperformer * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: National Bank Financial ups target to C$193 from C$181  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Alimentation Couche-Tard <ATDb.TO>: CIBC raises price target to c$34 from c$31.67 * Augusta Resource <AZC.TO>: CIBC cuts to sector performer from sector outperformer * Augusta Resource <AZC.TO>: CIBC cuts price target to C$3.56 from C$4.75  * Alaris Royalty <AD.TO>: Raymond James cuts target price to C$32.50 from C$33.50;outperform * Bonterra Energy <BNE.TO>: CIBC raises price target to c$74 from c$68  * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: National Bank Financial ups target to C$193 from C$181